te: New Lead Form Submission"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp & Shape Lead\n\nShapes the item: writes `leadId`, `receivedAt`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Payload Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"1de80156-e1ff-eb8e-0718-3aab29408d75","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Lead"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.leadId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Prepare Approval Packet · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"eba83c12-46c8-d69a-b072-e1d3cd6c36f1","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"ebc41ea7-e144-6a47-bcb9-866249f7a180","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Prepare Approval Packet\n\nShapes the item: writes `requestId`, `summary`, `requestedBy`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Request Approval via Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"f3eea5ec-0cde-63bb-354f-0ccb249b2435","name":"Note: Prepare Approval Packet"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Request Approval via Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Hold for Decision · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"31ef054f-4f6a-10a1-28d1-2b3bc12bb904","name":"Note: Request Approval via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold for Decision\n\nPauses the execution until the resume webhook is called — this is the approval/HITL gate.\n\nNext: Approved?","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"f509eb35-478c-7df1-379c-aeeed0bfb662","name":"Note: Hold for Decision"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Approved?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.body?.decision || $json.decision }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Execute Approved Action (API) · ②→ Record Decline + Notify Requester","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,520],"id":"26cc38ca-a3b9-354e-503f-29779e22f890","name":"Note: Approved?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Execute Approved Action (API)\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/leads — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Decision Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,280],"id":"c190aa81-dc54-0709-b57b-bc68d3094f60","name":"Note: Execute Approved Action (API)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Decline + Notify Requester\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Decision Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,880],"id":"34999ea2-ef83-3ea2-fab7-43ae31f50f7b","name":"Note: Record Decline + Notify Requester"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Join Decision Paths\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,520],"id":"4024bea7-785d-36ca-cbcb-2a0eea26631f","name":"Note: Join Decision Paths"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"45f9fce6-74b1-9c6b-5d8b-f54eefdbd83f","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"80d73107-9964-e105-669a-73eaea6e7f69","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"fb499dbf-ef2a-7a09-5b8a-6d6bfce8b5c4","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fingerprint for Idempotency · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"2b4f4fc2-7a48-4d10-88bc-9123a512f006","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per lead (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"ad977d5a-f635-6fa2-4cdc-52900d777177","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"8f239fc6-b32a-f6e4-e85c-6a9c4e540bf5","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"03a70be9-560b-078e-10a5-1e8083febbc4","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"1e6cbae8-a3a8-7eb1-de38-bad6a708d843","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nReads every row from 'Lead Tracker' — the read side of the store, e.g. for a digest or a downstream sync.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"1a8d27fb-43ce-2cae-22e6-f5bff15955e3","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"3acaa73f-44ac-3f35-1c31-3978ee007a18","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"634e2c2d-221b-1561-d0fa-1a5d389646e9","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Leads Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"dbc8eee7-9be5-7b12-804a-82db98a74037","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Leads Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty email","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"02ccad9c-e879-ab4c-d375-1a37ad690cc3","name":"Note: Sort Leads Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty email\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"b86e37b0-84dc-67e0-d38e-97db85977666","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty email"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"bd232b33-37ba-a88d-df57-018c6e1b61fd","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 25 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"e2ce10b2-29af-605e-2284-f9b0b26f8896","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"8942138e-77fa-4095-c2d1-ca7bef66afd7","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Lead Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"e08253cb-8aa0-7bbe-3b9f-6c091ba256f6","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"442788ed-c129-91a5-0279-9ff3f59c6972","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,1540],"id":"fe224344-2816-2f40-bdc1-a1b067eb3511","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,1540],"id":"57b3d6e1-b045-1ae6-504d-6f243b200b25","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"2b26020c-f586-3d24-1853-9344d8a3649c","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Log applications with Google Sheets and Slack\n\n**Pattern:** Form Intake · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nLog applications with Google Sheets and Slack. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual outreach is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Lead Form Submission → Stamp & Shape Lead → Payload Valid? → Prepare Approval Packet → Request Approval via Slack → Hold for Decision → Approved? → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to form intake without manual effort\n- Anyone automating outreach in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Improves response time\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"25a981ea-4f0a-acb2-59b9-61074896ce9c","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nThe workflow pauses on a Wait node configured to resume via webhook — n8n's actual human-in-the-loop primitive, not a polling loop. The resume URL is embedded directly in the approval message so approving is one click, and the paused execution burns no compute for however long the decision takes.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"3c9ff634-246f-6e97-b846-99bb32677924","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Add a timeout to the Wait node so unanswered approvals auto-decline after N hours.\n2. Change the approval channel and confirm the resume link still works.\n3. Add a third outcome (e.g. 'needs changes') alongside approve/decline.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"58b27f64-7737-286e-0a72-71294a68daae","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"8888a0bc-eab5-f99e-80d8-43e37d0bb34f","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"383f03fc-175f-046d-b248-72d758000e8b","name":"⏱ Rate limiting"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🙋 Human in the loop\n\nThe workflow pauses at the Wait node until a human posts a decision to the resume URL (included in the approval message). Approve → the action executes; anything else → recorded as declined. No timeout is set by default — add one under the Wait node's options if approvals go stale.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"97266be1-3f37-d7af-7655-a57b333060f6","name":"🙋 Human in the loop"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your outreach process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"3504994b-a389-96eb-2a27-77be3ae0c4b1","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"New Lead Form Submission":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Lead","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Lead":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Prepare Approval Packet","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Prepare Approval Packet":{"main":[[{"node":"Request Approval via Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Request Approval via Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Hold for Decision","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hold for Decision":{"main":[[{"node":"Approved?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Approved?":{"main":[[{"node":"Execute Approved Action (API)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Decline + Notify Requester","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Execute Approved Action (API)":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Decision Paths","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Decline + Notify Requester":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Decision Paths","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Join Decision Paths":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Leads Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Leads Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty email","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty email":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"New Lead Form Submission":[{"json":{"leadId":"LEAD-8801","email":"tom.becker@innotech.com","company":"InnoTech Solutions","score":82}},{"json":{"leadId":"LEAD-8802","email":"grace.kim@harborworks.com","company":"Harborworks","score":47}}]},"versionId":"2d0e9e3a-9e9b-4377-aaa7-cc37988b588d","id":"FDX04245"}